      "AI_Summary": "• Tesla does not require a single EU-wide approval to sell its Full Self-Driving (Supervised) software in Europe; it can pursue country-by-country approvals.\n• The Netherlands has already approved Tesla's FSD (Supervised) via its Vehicle Authority (RDW), setting a precedent for other countries.\n• An EU-wide vote on FSD (Supervised) approval is anticipated in July, but individual countries can grant provisional approvals based on existing data, potentially speeding up market entry.\n• The approval of FSD (Supervised) is considered a key catalyst for Tesla's stock, paving the way for potential robotaxi approvals in the future.",
